to pull you out.
-You can't --

11:37.831 --> 11:39.299
Don't listen to Steve!

11:39.399 --> 11:41.568
He's been seduced by
the hall monitor lifestyle.

11:41.668 --> 11:43.236
I have not.

11:43.336 --> 11:44.704
Then you won't
have a problem...

11:44.805 --> 11:45.906
wearing a wire.

11:46.006 --> 11:48.375
Ooh, tonight's
bad for a wire.

11:48.475 --> 11:50.077
We have a big dinner
with Lewis.

11:50.177 --> 11:52.145
L-Let's pencil it in
for after Labor Day.

11:52.245 --> 11:55.949
That would give me a chance
to focus on the sex dance.

11:56.049 --> 11:57.150
Steve doesn't want
to catch Lewis

11:57.250 --> 11:58.952
because he's
in too deep.

11:59.052 --> 12:00.553
Right.
Steve wears the wire.

12:00.653 --> 12:01.621
Tonight.

12:01.721 --> 12:02.890
Fine.

12:02.990 --> 12:03.891
I'm coming with.

12:04.024 --> 12:06.559
And if we get in trouble,
I have cyanide pills.

12:06.659 --> 12:08.962
We cannot fall
into enemy hands.

12:09.062 --> 12:11.298
Wait, they look just like
my Tic Tacs.

12:11.398 --> 12:13.300
Why did I mix them together?

12:13.400 --> 12:17.938
Oh, man, I was handing these out
like crazy at the post office.

12:18.038 --> 12:20.340
**

12:20.440 --> 12:21.842
(laughter)

12:21.942 --> 12:24.511
Damn, guys.
Smith cracks me up!

12:24.611 --> 12:26.479
KLAUS: They're on to us.
We got no way out.

12:26.579 --> 12:28.181
Take the pill.

12:28.281 --> 12:30.017
