when I was wasted

12:35.522 --> 12:36.990
and bought
a Christmas tree farm.

12:37.090 --> 12:39.827
But that thing makes no money
11 months a year!

12:39.927 --> 12:42.529
I had to find a way
to make money year round,

12:42.629 --> 12:46.166
so I cooked up
this totally illegal idea.

12:46.266 --> 12:47.700
Hold that thought,
I gotta take a dump.

12:47.801 --> 12:49.803
Hold that dump,
I gotta share a thought.

12:49.903 --> 12:51.805
I've been grinding up
the trees for sawdust,

12:51.905 --> 12:53.273
but nobody
wanted this stuff.

12:53.373 --> 12:56.176
-(plates clatter)
-So I finally had the excuse

12:56.276 --> 12:58.946
to do something I've wanted
to do for years --

12:59.046 --> 13:00.680
poison children.

13:00.780 --> 13:03.216
Lots of vomit means
lots of sawdust.

13:03.316 --> 13:05.685
I-I don't think any of that
could be tied to you.

13:05.785 --> 13:07.387
But that was
small potatoes.

13:07.487 --> 13:09.456
This next part
is big potatoes.

13:09.556 --> 13:10.690
If someone were
to record it,

13:10.790 --> 13:12.125
there's not
a jury in the world

13:12.225 --> 13:14.727
that wouldn't lock me up
and throw away the key!

13:14.828 --> 13:17.865
I'm going to poison
the town's water supply!

13:17.965 --> 13:21.534
Me!
Principal Brian Lewis!

13:21.634 --> 13:23.170
Oh, boy.

13:23.270 --> 13:25.538
Oh, man.
What a sting.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.707
We got Lewis
dead to rights.

13:27.807 --> 13:29.309
Didn't you think some of
the things he said

13:29.409 --> 13:31.744
had a jokey,
inadmissible quality?

13:31.845 --> 13:34.147
Oh, no.
This is airtight.

13:34.247 --> 13:35.348
Whoo-hoo!

13:35.448 --> 13:36.917
I'm gonna hit the sack.

13:41.054 --> 13:42.089
KLAUS: I can't sleep.

13:42.189 --> 13:43.590
I'm buzzing.

13:43.690 --> 13:45.893
Where are those
cyanide pills?

13:45.993 --> 13:47.227
I'll just take
a little half.

13:47.327 --> 13:49.930
Slow down the old
super-computer.

13:50.030 --> 13:51.398
What are you doing?!

13:51.498 --> 13:52.532
I-I have to do it!

13:52.632 --> 13:54.434
I have to!
I'm in too deep!

13:54.534 --> 13:57.104
Before you do it, just let me
say three words to you --

13:57.204 --> 13:59.206
telescoping driving cane.

13:59.306 --> 14:00.773
That means
nothing to me.

14:00.874 --> 14:03.043
Hi-yaaaa!

14:03.143 --> 14:04.912
(thud)

14:05.012 --> 14:07.080
He's coming to!

14:07.180 --> 14:08.882
STEVE: Wh-What's going on?

14:08.982 --> 14:11.284
These are the women
Lewis fired.

14:11.384 --> 14:14.621
They wander the streets,
still dressed as lunch ladies.

14:14.721 --> 14:17.124
They just want to put
slop on plates.

14:17.224 --> 14:18.926
Won't you help them,
Steve?

14:19.026 --> 14:20.560
I will.

14:20.660 --> 14:22.629
Your whack on the head
knocked some sense into me.

14:22.729 --> 14:24.697
We've got to get this
evidence to Turlington.

14:24.797 --> 14:27.434
I'll drive.

14:27.534 --> 14:30.037
Where does one buy
a telescoping driving cane?

14:30.137 --> 14:31.371
-Eddie Bauer.
-Oh.

14:31.471 --> 14:32.705
(both scream)

14:33.240 --> 14:34.374
(both scream)

14:34.474 --> 14:36.043
(light switch clicks)

14:36.143 --> 14:37.310
Do you think
it was suicide?

14:37.410 --> 14:38.811
At least we have
the recording.

14:38.912 --> 14:40.447
We can still take it
to the cops.

14:40.547 --> 14:43.450
We should
close his eyes.

14:43.550 --> 14:44.784
Oh, shit.

14:44.884 --> 14:47.120
This freak doesn't have
any eyelids.

14:47.220 --> 14:48.155
(telephone ringing)

14:48.255 --> 14:49.622
Gather round.

14:49.722 --> 14:51.458
All you cops are gonna want
to hear this.

14:51.558 --> 14:53.493
Yeah, so put down your
doughnuts, piggies,

14:53.593 --> 14:54.661
and listen up!

14:58.131 --> 15:00.600
KLAUS: (groaning)

15:00.700 --> 15:02.302
It's so dang hot under this.

15:02.402 --> 15:03.803
I'm dying.

15:03.903 --> 15:06.806
Why did I guzzle
that Arizona Iced Tea?

15:06.906 --> 15:08.441
(click, rewinding)

15:08.541 --> 15:11.945
Steve's wearing a jacket
and a long-sleeve tee?

15:12.045 --> 15:13.646
What is wrong with him?

15:13.746 --> 15:16.616
(sighs) Well,
we have nothing.

15:16.716 --> 15:18.085
Wait,
don't turn it off.

15:18.185 --> 15:20.487
I'm about to sing a song
from Wicked.

15:20.587 --> 15:22.455
KLAUS: The wizard
is ready for you.

15:22.555 --> 15:26.026
(vocalizing)

15:28.828 --> 15:30.863
**

15:30.964 --> 15:31.864
Turlington's dead,

15:31.965 --> 15:33.700
the whole town's about
to get poisoned --

15:33.800 --> 15:35.002
(cellphone chimes)

15:35.102 --> 15:38.005
And now Lewis wants
to take me up to the tree farm.

15:38.105 --> 15:39.706
Oh, God!
He's gonna kill me!

15:39.806 --> 15:42.009
No. He's gonna kill us.

15:42.109 --> 15:43.510
You're not coming.

15:43.610 --> 15:46.546
It's sweet of you to worry
about me, but I'm coming.

15:46.646 --> 15:48.181
Fine.
But to be clear,

15:48.281 --> 15:49.849
I wasn't trying
to keep you safe.

15:49.949 --> 15:51.818
I just didn't want
to be around you.

15:51.918 --> 15:53.686
Your little bowl
bothers me.

15:53.786 --> 15:55.488
All the scooting
and scraping.

15:55.588 --> 15:57.824
It's...very unpleasant.

15:57.924 --> 16:01.828
**

16:01.928 --> 16:03.663
I thought it was
about time you all saw

16:03.763 --> 16:04.864
where
the magic happens.

16:04.964 --> 16:06.399
I call it magic
because I don't know

16:06.499 --> 16:08.535
what any
of these machines do.

16:08.635 --> 16:12.339
I have a bunch of fat guys who
make the machines eat the trees.

16:12.439 --> 16:14.007
They're so fat.

16:14.107 --> 16:15.408
You should see
their work pants.

16:15.508 --> 16:17.510
The size!
When they hang them up to dry,

16:17.610 --> 16:19.646
they look like
medieval tapestries!

16:19.746 --> 16:22.082
Some of them
are truly gorgeous.

16:23.216 --> 16:25.885
I'm gonna sneak off
and do some recon.

16:25.985 --> 16:27.887
Klaus,
it's super-dangerous.

16:27.987 --> 16:28.888
Don't worry.

16:28.988 --> 16:31.524
Ol' Klaus can
take care of himself.

16:31.624 --> 16:33.393
* Bum-bum-bum-bum
bum-bum-bum-bum *

16:33.493 --> 16:34.427
Shh!

16:34.527 --> 16:37.197
* Bwaaaaa bwaaa! *

16:37.297 --> 16:40.200
* Bwaaaa, bwah-bwah! *

16:40.300 --> 16:41.934
KLAUS: Oop! I've been
caught immediately!

16:42.035 --> 16:43.270
No!
Not the toilet!

16:43.370 --> 16:45.238
(toilet flushes)

16:45.338 --> 16:49.609
**

16:49.709 --> 16:51.111
This isn't
funny anymore.

16:51.211 --> 16:53.846
We gotta do something
about these Catatonic Cathys.

16:53.946 --> 16:55.448
It's been days.

16:56.683 --> 16:57.850
Okay, that was
a little funny.

16:57.950 --> 16:59.352
-(knock on door)
-Don't worry, Mom.

16:59.452 --> 17:00.420
I called in some help.

17:00.520 --> 17:02.755
FRANCINE: Dr. Ray?

17:02.855 --> 17:04.691
I-I thought you died.

17:04.791 --> 17:06.393
-No.
-Oh, okay.

17:06.493 --> 17:08.461
Let's see
what we've got here.

17:08.561 --> 17:09.629
Mm-hmm.

17:09.729 --> 17:11.364
With extreme cases
like this,

17:11.464 --> 17:14.901
I find that returning to
the scene of the initial event

17:15.001 --> 17:18.271
sometimes helps snap
the patient out of it.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.940
How long could
this take?

17:21.040 --> 17:22.809
I don't know.
I gave up 30 minutes ago.

17:22.909 --> 17:24.711
Ooh!
A Cinnabon!

17:24.811 --> 17:26.879
I have one last idea.

17:28.948 --> 17:33.553
(rock music plays)

17:33.653 --> 17:35.655
* Come, my lady,
come, come, my lady *

17:35.755 --> 17:37.090
* You're my butterfly,
sugar, baby *

17:37.190 --> 17:40.059
* Come, my lady,
come, come, my lady *

17:40.160 --> 17:42.262
* You're my butterfly,
sugar, baby *

17:42.362 --> 17:44.397
* Such a sexy, sexy,
pretty little thing *

17:44.497 --> 17:45.398
* Fierce nipple pierce *

17:45.698 --> 17:47.300
* You got me sprung
with your tongue ring *

17:47.400 --> 17:49.402
* And I ain't gonna lie 'cause
your living gets me high *

17:49.502 --> 17:50.770
* So to keep you by my side *

17:50.870 --> 17:52.339
* There's nothing
that I won't try *

17:52.439 --> 17:54.474
* Butterflies in her eyes
and looks to kill *

17:54.574 --> 17:56.776
* Time is passing I'm asking
"Could this be real?" *

17:56.876 --> 17:58.611
* 'Cause I can't sleep,
I can't hold still *

17:58.711 --> 18:00.847
* The only thing I really know
is she got sex appeal *

18:00.947 --> 18:02.982
* I can feel,
too much is never enough *

18:03.082 --> 18:05.185
Well, I'm out
of ideas.

18:05.285 --> 18:06.786
Give it up, you guys!

18:06.886 --> 18:08.788
They're gonna be
vegetables forever!

18:08.888 --> 18:11.424
(screams)

18:11.524 --> 18:13.960
(screaming continues)

18:16.963 --> 18:18.331
Oh, hey, fun.

18:18.431 --> 18:20.200
The whole family's mall walking.

18:20.300 --> 18:23.170
What do you think?
Could old Al use a few laps?

18:23.270 --> 18:24.604
(chuckles)

18:24.704 --> 18:26.673
Do you even hear yourself?
"Oh, hey, fun.

18:26.773 --> 18:28.007
The whole family's mall walking.

18:28.107 --> 18:29.876
Yeah."
Oh, you're the town fool.

18:29.976 --> 18:31.978
Just get of here
with your dignity.

18:32.078 --> 18:33.980
Smell ya on the flip side,
skater bois.

18:34.080 --> 18:36.349
What the hell was that?

18:36.449 --> 18:38.351
**

18:38.451 --> 18:40.220
Huh? Huh?

18:40.320 --> 18:42.522
Ha. Those are funny.

18:42.622 --> 18:44.191
They're not supposed
to be funny.

18:44.291 --> 18:45.992
I think they're
incredibly moving.

18:46.092 --> 18:50.163
And now for the main event --
making the whole town puke.

18:50.263 --> 18:52.632
With this gross stuff
I found in my trunk.

18:52.732 --> 18:54.667
-(hissing)
-ALL: Ugh!

18:54.767 --> 18:58.838
This pipe leads directly
to the town's water supply.

18:58.938 --> 19:01.040
-(gasping)
-You think that's bad?

19:01.140 --> 19:02.875
Get ready to gasp again.

19:02.975 --> 19:05.144
There's a mole among our ranks.

19:05.245 --> 19:06.145
(gasping)

19:06.246 --> 19:07.380
(gasps)

19:07.480 --> 19:09.382
This is Turlington's phone,

19:09.482 --> 19:13.886
and this is the contact labeled
"hall monitor spy."

19:13.986 --> 19:16.856
(cellphone beeps, ringing)

19:16.956 --> 19:18.691
We could have made
a great team, Smith.

19:18.791 --> 19:21.194
But instead, you chose to be
murdered by your classmates.

19:21.294 --> 19:22.362
Get him!

19:24.431 --> 19:26.266
STEVE: You almost thought
of everything, Lewis.

19:26.366 --> 19:29.536
But there's one thing you forgot
to have thought of --

19:29.636 --> 19:33.340
in juvie,
I only worked out my legs!

19:33.440 --> 19:34.374
(grunts)

19:34.474 --> 19:38.077
(triumphant music plays)

19:38.177 --> 19:39.078
Ooh!

19:39.178 --> 19:40.179
(thud)

19:40.280 --> 19:42.682
(gasping)

19:42.782 --> 19:44.717
Lewis, you've poisoned
your last person...

19:44.817 --> 19:46.953
(stomach grumbling)

19:47.053 --> 19:48.087
...me.

19:48.187 --> 19:49.222
(door slams open)

19:49.322 --> 19:51.391
Hold it right there!

19:51.491 --> 19:53.593
Hey! I thought
we flushed you!

19:53.693 --> 19:57.464
When you flush,
you've gotta check the bowl.

19:57.564 --> 19:59.899
Lunch ladies, attack!

19:59.999 --> 20:00.967
**

20:01.067 --> 20:03.202
-(grunts)
-Oh!

20:04.136 --> 20:05.071
(grunts)

20:05.171 --> 20:06.739
**

20:06.839 --> 20:08.241
(thudding, pots clanging)

20:08.341 --> 20:10.243
Ooh! (groans)

20:10.343 --> 20:12.379
(retches)

20:12.479 --> 20:14.281
**

20:14.381 --> 20:15.982
Aah!

20:16.082 --> 20:18.385
(grunts) Aaah!

20:19.986 --> 20:22.489
Aaah!

20:22.589 --> 20:24.090
(thudding, crashing)

20:26.726 --> 20:28.761
Wh-Wh-What happened?

20:28.861 --> 20:30.096
Easy, bud.

20:30.196 --> 20:32.499
You're home safe
in the school cafeteria.

20:32.599 --> 20:34.267
Wh-What's going
in my arm?

20:34.367 --> 20:36.002
You lost a lot of fluids,

20:36.102 --> 20:38.638
so Agnes put you
on a Salisbury IV.

20:38.738 --> 20:41.774
Look, the brown's returning
to your cheeks already.

20:41.874 --> 20:45.445
Thanks for saving me
from Lewis, and from myself.

20:45.545 --> 20:47.146
Hey, what happened
to Lewis?

20:47.246 --> 20:48.748
He got away basically.

20:48.848 --> 20:51.083
Lewis gets away again!

20:51.183 --> 20:53.252
Hey, you wanna buy
a mattress factory?

20:53.353 --> 20:56.188
(bleep) yeah, I do!

20:56.289 --> 20:57.824
(gasps)

20:57.924 --> 20:58.825
Billy?

20:58.925 --> 21:02.128
I had
the premonition again.

21:02.228 --> 21:04.130
Bye!
Have a beautiful time!

21:06.198 --> 21:08.000
-- Captions by VITAC --
